Creating interactive plots

Benjamin Guiastrennec

11 May, 2017

Warning

Please note that this feature is experimental and not all aspects of ggplot2 are supported by ploty! To learn more about plotly you visit this page.

Install plotly

This command is only required for the first use.

install.packages("plotly")

Load packages

Start by loading the plotly and xpose packages.

library(plotly)
library(xpose)

Generate a plot with xpose

Then generate any plot in xpose and store it in an object.

gof_plot <- dv_vs_ipred(xpdb_ex_pk, type = 'pl',
                        aes(point_color = as.factor(SEX), 
                            line_color = as.factor(SEX))) +
             labs(color = 'Sex')

Convert the plot from ggplot2 to plotly

The ggplot2 object is now automatically conveted to a plotly graph. The scales can now be changed interactively, groups can be hidden by clicking on the legend

plotly::ggplotly(gof_plot)
